abstract: Kamala Harris is out of the race. We diagnosed her messaging missteps with our colleague Astead W. Herndon.
snippet: Kamala Harris is out of the race. We diagnosed her messaging missteps with our colleague Astead W. Herndon.
lead_paragraph: Hi. Welcome to On Politics, your guide to the day in national politics. I’m Nick Corasaniti, your host on Tuesdays for our coverage of all things media and messaging.

abstract: She was crowned the perfect Democrat for 2020. Here’s what doomed her campaign.
snippet: She was crowned the perfect Democrat for 2020. Here’s what doomed her campaign.
lead_paragraph: OAKLAND, Calif. — Just as California is so often viewed from afar as either glittering paradise or dystopian disaster, so Kamala Harris was crowned as the perfect Democrat for 2020.

headline_main: Uighurs, China Trade, NATO: Your Wednesday Briefing

abstract: The California senator broke barriers but ran out of money as she struggled in polls. Her abrupt announcement is perhaps the most surprising development to date in the 2020 race.
snippet: The California senator broke barriers but ran out of money as she struggled in polls. Her abrupt announcement is perhaps the most surprising development to date in the 2020 race.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris of California dropped out of the Democratic presidential race on Tuesday after months of low poll numbers and a series of missteps that crippled her campaign, a deflating comedown for a barrier-breaking candidate who was seeking to become the first black woman to win a major party’s presidential nomination.

abstract: The senator unveiled a broad plan at a decisive period for his struggling campaign as he faces the prospect of not making the December debate.
snippet: The senator unveiled a broad plan at a decisive period for his struggling campaign as he faces the prospect of not making the December debate.
lead_paragraph: Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey on Tuesday proposed investing $100 billion in historically black colleges and universities and other minority-serving institutions, a broad proposal in a Democratic field that has offered varying plans to prop up this longstanding yet struggling arm of the educational system.

abstract: The Democrats need a unifier. It could be the Vermont Socialist.
snippet: The Democrats need a unifier. It could be the Vermont Socialist.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic Party needs a nominee, but right now it has a train wreck instead. The front-runner seems too old for the job and is poised to lose the first two primary season contests. The woman who was supposed to become the front-runner on the basis of her policy chops is sliding in the polls after thoroughly botching her health care strategy. The candidate rising in her place is a 37-year-old mayor of a tiny, not-obviously-thriving city.
